{"type":"data","nodes":[null,{"type":"data","data":[{"tree":1},[2,26,45,59],{"slug":3,"title":4,"pages":5},"start","Start",[6,14,20],{"siteId":7,"section":3,"slug":8,"path":9,"title":10,"description":11,"order":12,"verified":13},"claw","install","/content/claw/docs/start/install.md","Install","Get the NullClaw binary via Homebrew, Docker, or a source build with Zig 0.16.0.",1,"v2026.5.29",{"siteId":7,"section":3,"slug":15,"path":16,"title":17,"description":18,"order":19,"verified":13},"quickstart","/content/claw/docs/start/quickstart.md","Quickstart","From a fresh install to a first conversation and a running gateway.",2,{"siteId":7,"section":3,"slug":21,"path":22,"title":23,"description":24,"order":25,"verified":13},"first-channel","/content/claw/docs/start/first-channel.md","Your first channel","Connect NullClaw to Telegram (or any of the 26 channels) and lock it down with allowlists.",3,{"slug":27,"title":28,"pages":29},"configure","Configure",[30,35,40],{"siteId":7,"section":27,"slug":31,"path":32,"title":33,"description":34,"order":12,"verified":13},"configuration","/content/claw/docs/configure/configuration.md","Configuration","One JSON file at ~/.nullclaw/config.json — OpenClaw-compatible, snake_case, no magic.",{"siteId":7,"section":27,"slug":36,"path":37,"title":38,"description":39,"order":19,"verified":13},"providers","/content/claw/docs/configure/providers.md","Providers","Connect ~60 model providers, set the default route, and add fallbacks and auto-routing.",{"siteId":7,"section":27,"slug":41,"path":42,"title":43,"description":44,"order":25,"verified":13},"memory","/content/claw/docs/configure/memory.md","Memory","Hybrid search over SQLite by default, nine other engines when you need them, and CLI tools to keep it clean.",{"slug":46,"title":47,"pages":48},"operate","Operate",[49,54],{"siteId":7,"section":46,"slug":50,"path":51,"title":52,"description":53,"order":12,"verified":13},"gateway-and-service","/content/claw/docs/operate/gateway-and-service.md","Gateway and service","Run NullClaw long-term — the HTTP gateway, pairing, cron endpoints, and background service mode.",{"siteId":7,"section":46,"slug":55,"path":56,"title":57,"description":58,"order":19,"verified":13},"security","/content/claw/docs/operate/security.md","Security","The layers NullClaw enforces by default, the settings that widen them, and how to audit for leaked secrets.",{"slug":60,"title":61,"pages":62},"reference","Reference",[63],{"siteId":7,"section":60,"slug":64,"path":65,"title":66,"description":67,"order":12,"verified":13},"cli","/content/claw/docs/reference/cli.md","CLI reference","Every nullclaw command, grouped by task — setup, runtime, channels, cron, memory, automation flags, and build flags."],"uses":{}},{"type":"data","data":[{"doc":1,"raw":10,"dateModified":35,"sectionTitle":36,"prev":37,"next":38},{"siteId":2,"section":3,"slug":4,"path":5,"title":6,"description":7,"order":8,"verified":9,"body":10,"html":11,"toc":12},"claw","start","install","/content/claw/docs/start/install.md","Install","Get the NullClaw binary via Homebrew, Docker, or a source build with Zig 0.16.0.",1,"v2026.5.29","\nNullClaw ships as a single static binary with no runtime dependencies besides libc. Pick one of the paths below and you are done in a minute or two.\n\n> [!NOTE]\n> Pre-1.0: config and CLI may change between releases.\n\n## Homebrew (recommended for macOS and Linux)\n\n```bash\nbrew install nullclaw\nnullclaw --help\n```\n\nIf the help output prints, the install is complete.\n\nTo upgrade later:\n\n```bash\nbrew update\nbrew upgrade nullclaw\n```\n\n## Docker or Podman\n\nNullClaw publishes an official OCI image at `ghcr.io/nullclaw/nullclaw`. The container keeps all persistent state under `/nullclaw-data` — config at `/nullclaw-data/config.json`, workspace at `/nullclaw-data/workspace`.\n\n```bash\n# one-off command\ndocker run --rm -it \\\n  -v nullclaw-data:/nullclaw-data \\\n  ghcr.io/nullclaw/nullclaw:latest status\n\n# initialize config interactively\ndocker run --rm -it \\\n  -v nullclaw-data:/nullclaw-data \\\n  ghcr.io/nullclaw/nullclaw:latest onboard --interactive\n\n# run the HTTP gateway on host loopback\ndocker run --rm -it \\\n  -p 127.0.0.1:3000:3000 \\\n  -v nullclaw-data:/nullclaw-data \\\n  ghcr.io/nullclaw/nullclaw:latest\n```\n\nThe repository also ships a Makefile wrapper around Docker Compose:\n\n```bash\nmake build\nmake config\nmake up\n```\n\n`make config` runs `nullclaw onboard --interactive` inside the container. Pass only non-secret flags through `CONFIG_ARGS` — command-line arguments can leak via shell history and process listings:\n\n```bash\nmake config CONFIG_ARGS=\"--provider openrouter\"\n```\n\n## Build from source\n\nYou need **Zig 0.16.0 exactly**. Other versions are unsupported and may fail to build. Check first:\n\n```bash\nzig version   # must print 0.16.0\n```\n\nThen:\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/nullclaw/nullclaw.git\ncd nullclaw\nzig build -Doptimize=ReleaseSmall\nzig build test --summary all\n```\n\nThe binary lands at `zig-out/bin/nullclaw`. To put it on your `PATH`:\n\n```bash\nzig build -Doptimize=ReleaseSmall -p \"$HOME/.local\"\necho 'export PATH=\"$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH\"' >> ~/.zshrc\n# bash users: ~/.bashrc\n```\n\n## Android / Termux\n\nOfficial releases include pre-built Android/Termux binaries for `aarch64`, `armv7`, and `x86_64`. You can also build natively on the device:\n\n```bash\npkg update\npkg install git zig\ngit clone https://github.com/nullclaw/nullclaw.git\ncd nullclaw\nzig build -Doptimize=ReleaseSmall\n./zig-out/bin/nullclaw --help\n```\n\nOn Android, prefer foreground use (`agent`, `gateway`) before trying service mode.\n\n## Verify\n\n```bash\nnullclaw --help\nnullclaw --version\nnullclaw status\n```\n\nIf `status` returns component state, the runtime basics are ready.\n\n## Keeping it current\n\nThe binary can update itself:\n\n```bash\nnullclaw update --check   # check only\nnullclaw update --yes     # install without prompting\n```\n\nReleases use CalVer tags (`vYYYY.M.D`); `nullclaw --version` prints the version embedded from the git tag.\n\n## Next\n\nContinue with [Quickstart](/docs/start/quickstart/) to onboard a provider and send your first message.\n","\u003Cp>NullClaw ships as a single static binary with no runtime dependencies besides libc. Pick one of the paths below and you are done in a minute or two.\u003C/p>\n\u003Caside class=\"callout callout--note\">\u003Cdiv class=\"callout-title\">Note\u003C/div>\u003Cp>Pre-1.0: config and CLI may change between releases.\u003C/p>\n\u003C/aside>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"homebrew-recommended-for-macos-and-linux\" aria-labelledby=\"heading-label-homebrew-recommended-for-macos-and-linux\">\u003Cspan id=\"heading-label-homebrew-recommended-for-macos-and-linux\">Homebrew (recommended for macOS and Linux)\u003C/span>\u003Ca class=\"heading-anchor\" href=\"#homebrew-recommended-for-macos-and-linux\" aria-label=\"Permalink to Homebrew (recommended for macOS and Linux)\" data-pagefind-ignore>\u003Cspan aria-hidden=\"true\">#\u003C/span>\u003C/a>\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cfigure class=\"code-figure\" data-lang=\"bash\">\u003Cpre class=\"shiki null-kitchen\" style=\"background-color:#0a0806;color:#d9d1c3\" tabindex=\"0\">\u003Ccode>\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">brew\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> install\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> nullclaw\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">nullclaw\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> --help\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\u003Cbutton class=\"code-copy\" type=\"button\" data-code data-pagefind-ignore aria-live=\"polite\">copy\u003C/button>\u003C/figure>\n\u003Cp>If the help output prints, the install is complete.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>To upgrade later:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cfigure class=\"code-figure\" data-lang=\"bash\">\u003Cpre class=\"shiki null-kitchen\" style=\"background-color:#0a0806;color:#d9d1c3\" tabindex=\"0\">\u003Ccode>\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">brew\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> update\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">brew\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> upgrade\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> nullclaw\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\u003Cbutton class=\"code-copy\" type=\"button\" data-code data-pagefind-ignore aria-live=\"polite\">copy\u003C/button>\u003C/figure>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"docker-or-podman\" aria-labelledby=\"heading-label-docker-or-podman\">\u003Cspan id=\"heading-label-docker-or-podman\">Docker or Podman\u003C/span>\u003Ca class=\"heading-anchor\" href=\"#docker-or-podman\" aria-label=\"Permalink to Docker or Podman\" data-pagefind-ignore>\u003Cspan aria-hidden=\"true\">#\u003C/span>\u003C/a>\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>NullClaw publishes an official OCI image at \u003Ccode>ghcr.io/nullclaw/nullclaw\u003C/code>. The container keeps all persistent state under \u003Ccode>/nullclaw-data\u003C/code> — config at \u003Ccode>/nullclaw-data/config.json\u003C/code>, workspace at \u003Ccode>/nullclaw-data/workspace\u003C/code>.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cfigure class=\"code-figure\" data-lang=\"bash\">\u003Cpre class=\"shiki null-kitchen\" style=\"background-color:#0a0806;color:#d9d1c3\" tabindex=\"0\">\u003Ccode>\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#877E6F;font-style:italic\"># one-off command\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">docker\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> run\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> --rm\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> -it\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#D9A441\"> \\\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\">  -v\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> nullclaw-data:/nullclaw-data\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#D9A441\"> \\\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\">  ghcr.io/nullclaw/nullclaw:latest\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> status\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#877E6F;font-style:italic\"># initialize config interactively\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">docker\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> run\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> --rm\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> -it\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#D9A441\"> \\\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\">  -v\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> nullclaw-data:/nullclaw-data\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#D9A441\"> \\\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\">  ghcr.io/nullclaw/nullclaw:latest\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> onboard\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> --interactive\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#877E6F;font-style:italic\"># run the HTTP gateway on host loopback\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">docker\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> run\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> --rm\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> -it\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#D9A441\"> \\\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\">  -p\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> 127.0.0.1:3000:3000\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#D9A441\"> \\\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\">  -v\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> nullclaw-data:/nullclaw-data\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#D9A441\"> \\\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\">  ghcr.io/nullclaw/nullclaw:latest\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\u003Cbutton class=\"code-copy\" type=\"button\" data-code data-pagefind-ignore aria-live=\"polite\">copy\u003C/button>\u003C/figure>\n\u003Cp>The repository also ships a Makefile wrapper around Docker Compose:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cfigure class=\"code-figure\" data-lang=\"bash\">\u003Cpre class=\"shiki null-kitchen\" style=\"background-color:#0a0806;color:#d9d1c3\" tabindex=\"0\">\u003Ccode>\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">make\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> build\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">make\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> config\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">make\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> up\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\u003Cbutton class=\"code-copy\" type=\"button\" data-code data-pagefind-ignore aria-live=\"polite\">copy\u003C/button>\u003C/figure>\n\u003Cp>\u003Ccode>make config\u003C/code> runs \u003Ccode>nullclaw onboard --interactive\u003C/code> inside the container. Pass only non-secret flags through \u003Ccode>CONFIG_ARGS\u003C/code> — command-line arguments can leak via shell history and process listings:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cfigure class=\"code-figure\" data-lang=\"bash\">\u003Cpre class=\"shiki null-kitchen\" style=\"background-color:#0a0806;color:#d9d1c3\" tabindex=\"0\">\u003Ccode>\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">make\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> config\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> CONFIG_ARGS=\"--provider openrouter\"\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\u003Cbutton class=\"code-copy\" type=\"button\" data-code data-pagefind-ignore aria-live=\"polite\">copy\u003C/button>\u003C/figure>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"build-from-source\" aria-labelledby=\"heading-label-build-from-source\">\u003Cspan id=\"heading-label-build-from-source\">Build from source\u003C/span>\u003Ca class=\"heading-anchor\" href=\"#build-from-source\" aria-label=\"Permalink to Build from source\" data-pagefind-ignore>\u003Cspan aria-hidden=\"true\">#\u003C/span>\u003C/a>\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>You need \u003Cstrong>Zig 0.16.0 exactly\u003C/strong>. Other versions are unsupported and may fail to build. Check first:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cfigure class=\"code-figure\" data-lang=\"bash\">\u003Cpre class=\"shiki null-kitchen\" style=\"background-color:#0a0806;color:#d9d1c3\" tabindex=\"0\">\u003Ccode>\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">zig\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> version\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#877E6F;font-style:italic\">   # must print 0.16.0\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\u003Cbutton class=\"code-copy\" type=\"button\" data-code data-pagefind-ignore aria-live=\"polite\">copy\u003C/button>\u003C/figure>\n\u003Cp>Then:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cfigure class=\"code-figure\" data-lang=\"bash\">\u003Cpre class=\"shiki null-kitchen\" style=\"background-color:#0a0806;color:#d9d1c3\" tabindex=\"0\">\u003Ccode>\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">git\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> clone\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> https://github.com/nullclaw/nullclaw.git\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">cd\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> nullclaw\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">zig\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> build\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> -Doptimize=ReleaseSmall\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">zig\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> build\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> test\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> --summary\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> all\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\u003Cbutton class=\"code-copy\" type=\"button\" data-code data-pagefind-ignore aria-live=\"polite\">copy\u003C/button>\u003C/figure>\n\u003Cp>The binary lands at \u003Ccode>zig-out/bin/nullclaw\u003C/code>. To put it on your \u003Ccode>PATH\u003C/code>:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cfigure class=\"code-figure\" data-lang=\"bash\">\u003Cpre class=\"shiki null-kitchen\" style=\"background-color:#0a0806;color:#d9d1c3\" tabindex=\"0\">\u003Ccode>\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">zig\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> build\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> -Doptimize=ReleaseSmall\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> -p\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#D9D1C3\">$HOME\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\">/.local\"\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">echo\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> 'export PATH=\"$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH\"'\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#FF4F30\"> >>\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> ~/.zshrc\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#877E6F;font-style:italic\"># bash users: ~/.bashrc\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\u003Cbutton class=\"code-copy\" type=\"button\" data-code data-pagefind-ignore aria-live=\"polite\">copy\u003C/button>\u003C/figure>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"android-termux\" aria-labelledby=\"heading-label-android-termux\">\u003Cspan id=\"heading-label-android-termux\">Android / Termux\u003C/span>\u003Ca class=\"heading-anchor\" href=\"#android-termux\" aria-label=\"Permalink to Android / Termux\" data-pagefind-ignore>\u003Cspan aria-hidden=\"true\">#\u003C/span>\u003C/a>\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>Official releases include pre-built Android/Termux binaries for \u003Ccode>aarch64\u003C/code>, \u003Ccode>armv7\u003C/code>, and \u003Ccode>x86_64\u003C/code>. You can also build natively on the device:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cfigure class=\"code-figure\" data-lang=\"bash\">\u003Cpre class=\"shiki null-kitchen\" style=\"background-color:#0a0806;color:#d9d1c3\" tabindex=\"0\">\u003Ccode>\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">pkg\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> update\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">pkg\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> install\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> git\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> zig\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">git\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> clone\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> https://github.com/nullclaw/nullclaw.git\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">cd\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> nullclaw\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">zig\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> build\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> -Doptimize=ReleaseSmall\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">./zig-out/bin/nullclaw\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> --help\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\u003Cbutton class=\"code-copy\" type=\"button\" data-code data-pagefind-ignore aria-live=\"polite\">copy\u003C/button>\u003C/figure>\n\u003Cp>On Android, prefer foreground use (\u003Ccode>agent\u003C/code>, \u003Ccode>gateway\u003C/code>) before trying service mode.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"verify\" aria-labelledby=\"heading-label-verify\">\u003Cspan id=\"heading-label-verify\">Verify\u003C/span>\u003Ca class=\"heading-anchor\" href=\"#verify\" aria-label=\"Permalink to Verify\" data-pagefind-ignore>\u003Cspan aria-hidden=\"true\">#\u003C/span>\u003C/a>\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cfigure class=\"code-figure\" data-lang=\"bash\">\u003Cpre class=\"shiki null-kitchen\" style=\"background-color:#0a0806;color:#d9d1c3\" tabindex=\"0\">\u003Ccode>\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">nullclaw\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> --help\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">nullclaw\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> --version\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">nullclaw\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> status\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\u003Cbutton class=\"code-copy\" type=\"button\" data-code data-pagefind-ignore aria-live=\"polite\">copy\u003C/button>\u003C/figure>\n\u003Cp>If \u003Ccode>status\u003C/code> returns component state, the runtime basics are ready.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"keeping-it-current\" aria-labelledby=\"heading-label-keeping-it-current\">\u003Cspan id=\"heading-label-keeping-it-current\">Keeping it current\u003C/span>\u003Ca class=\"heading-anchor\" href=\"#keeping-it-current\" aria-label=\"Permalink to Keeping it current\" data-pagefind-ignore>\u003Cspan aria-hidden=\"true\">#\u003C/span>\u003C/a>\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>The binary can update itself:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cfigure class=\"code-figure\" data-lang=\"bash\">\u003Cpre class=\"shiki null-kitchen\" style=\"background-color:#0a0806;color:#d9d1c3\" tabindex=\"0\">\u003Ccode>\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">nullclaw\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> update\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> --check\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#877E6F;font-style:italic\">   # check only\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">nullclaw\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> update\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> --yes\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#877E6F;font-style:italic\">     # install without prompting\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\u003Cbutton class=\"code-copy\" type=\"button\" data-code data-pagefind-ignore aria-live=\"polite\">copy\u003C/button>\u003C/figure>\n\u003Cp>Releases use CalVer tags (\u003Ccode>vYYYY.M.D\u003C/code>); \u003Ccode>nullclaw --version\u003C/code> prints the version embedded from the git tag.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"next\" aria-labelledby=\"heading-label-next\">\u003Cspan id=\"heading-label-next\">Next\u003C/span>\u003Ca class=\"heading-anchor\" href=\"#next\" aria-label=\"Permalink to Next\" data-pagefind-ignore>\u003Cspan aria-hidden=\"true\">#\u003C/span>\u003C/a>\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>Continue with \u003Ca href=\"/docs/start/quickstart/\">Quickstart\u003C/a> to onboard a provider and send your first message.\u003C/p>\n",[13,17,20,23,26,29,32],{"id":14,"text":15,"depth":16},"homebrew-recommended-for-macos-and-linux","Homebrew (recommended for macOS and Linux)",2,{"id":18,"text":19,"depth":16},"docker-or-podman","Docker or Podman",{"id":21,"text":22,"depth":16},"build-from-source","Build from source",{"id":24,"text":25,"depth":16},"android-termux","Android / Termux",{"id":27,"text":28,"depth":16},"verify","Verify",{"id":30,"text":31,"depth":16},"keeping-it-current","Keeping it current",{"id":33,"text":34,"depth":16},"next","Next","2026-07-18","Start",null,{"siteId":2,"section":3,"slug":39,"path":40,"title":41,"description":42,"order":16,"verified":9,"sectionTitle":36},"quickstart","/content/claw/docs/start/quickstart.md","Quickstart","From a fresh install to a first conversation and a running gateway."],"uses":{"params":["section","slug"]}}]}
